10/02/2011
BANJA LUKA, Bosnia and Herzegovina (BiH) -- Serbia is interested in the prosperity and stability of Republika Srpska (RS) and BiH, Serbian Foreign Minister Vuk Jeremic said on Wednesday (February 9th) in Banja Luka after meeting with RS President Milorad Dodik. 
He also stressed the need to form governments at all levels in BiH, following the October general elections.
In other news Wednesday, Serbian Defence Minister Dragan Sutanovac announced plans to host a June a summit of NATO chiefs of general staff. 
Also attending will be representatives of Partnership for Peace programme countries. 
(B92, Beta, Danas, RTS, RTRS - 09/02/11)
